<br>
The behaviour of your members is everything.<br>
<br>
A lot of us have been burned in guilds before, both by joining a guild that turned out to be less well-behaved than we thought at first, and by a perfectly good guild being overrun by the poorly-behaved.  There are also some of us who have been burned in groups with (or by actions in the same zone as...) folks wearing guildtags.  I know the best thing to do would be to take it up with the guildleaders, just like the best thing to do when you receive poor service in RL is to take it up with the company.<br>
<br>
But what do most us do?  Nothing -- we just decide to avoid those folks in the future.  Unfortunately, that sometimes includes entire guilds.  I know we shouldn't make generalizations like that, but we still do.<br>
<br>
So now that I'm wondering if the right guild for me is already out there, I'm making a personal assessment of all the folks I've interacted with, as well as the tags above their heads.  Will I avoid those tags that have been over all the heads I didn't like?  Perhaps I shouldn't, but I probably will.  I just hope I don't pass up &quot;the right guild for me&quot; because of it.<br>
 <p>---<BR>
Kimaya Silverbark<BR>
